---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "All Endings Explained - Cyberpunk 2077 Complete Guide";
const description = "Every ending in Cyberpunk 2077 with exact requirements, decision points, and consequences. Unlock all endings and see what happens to V.";
---

<Layout {title} {description}>
  <article class="guide">
    <h1>🎬 All Endings Explained & How to Unlock Them</h1>

    <div class="intro">
      <p>Cyberpunk 2077 has 5 distinct endings (plus variations), each determined by your choices throughout the game. This guide covers every ending, how to unlock them, and what happens to V and the other characters. <strong>Massive spoilers ahead!</strong></p>

      <div class="warning-box">
        <strong>⚠️ SPOILER WARNING:</strong> This guide contains major spoilers for the entire game. If you haven't finished Cyberpunk 2077, you may want to play through first before reading.
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="endings-overview">
      <h2>📊 Endings Overview</h2>
      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Ending Name</th>
          <th>How to Unlock</th>
          <th>V's Fate</th>
          <th>Difficulty</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>The Star</strong></td>
          <td>Panam's questline + Aldecaldos</td>
          <td>Leaves Night City with the Aldecaldos</td>
          <td>⭐⭐</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>The Sun</strong></td>
          <td>Rogue's questline + Arasaka Tower assault</td>
          <td>Becomes a legend in the Afterlife</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>The Devil</strong></td>
          <td>Side with Hanako Arasaka</td>
          <td>Depends on final choice</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐⭐</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Temperance</strong></td>
          <td>Give your body to Johnny</td>
          <td>V dies, Johnny lives</td>
          <td>⭐⭐</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>(Don't Fear) The Reaper</strong></td>
          <td>Secret ending - High affinity with Johnny</td>
          <td>Solo assault on Arasaka Tower</td>
          <td>⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="detailed-endings">
      <h2>📖 Detailed Ending Breakdown</h2>

      <div class="ending-card">
        <h3>⭐ The Star Ending (Best Ending)</h3>
        <div class="ending-info">
          <p><strong>How to Unlock:</strong></p>
          <ol>
            <li>Complete Panam Palmer's full questline:
              <ul>
                <li>"Life During Wartime"</li>
                <li>"Riders on the Storm"</li>
                <li>"With a Little Help from My Friends"</li>
                <li>"Queen of the Highway"</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Maintain good relationship with Panam (make supportive dialogue choices)</li>
            <li>During "Nocturne Op55N1", choose to call Panam and ask the Aldecaldos for help</li>
            <li>Assault Arasaka Tower with the Aldecaldos</li>
            <li>At the finale, choose to enter the Well with Johnny</li>
            <li>Reject Arasaka's offer and choose to leave Night City</li>
          </ol>

          <p><strong>What Happens:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>V survives but has only 6 months to live (the Relic is too integrated)</li>
            <li>V leaves Night City with the Aldecaldos, searching for a way to remove the Relic</li>
            <li>Panam and the Aldecaldos become V's new family</li>
            <li>Johnny's engram is removed and destroyed</li>
            <li>V keeps all their relationships and friends</li>
          </ul>

          <p><strong>Why It's the Best:</strong> V has the highest chance of survival (the Aldecaldos have resources to help), and V leaves with a support network. It's the most hopeful ending.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ending-card">
        <h3>☀️ The Sun Ending (Legend of the Afterlife)</h3>
        <div class="ending-info">
          <p><strong>How to Unlock:</strong></p>
          <ol>
            <li>Complete Rogue Amendiares' full questline:
              <ul>
                <li>"Chippin' In"</li>
                <li>"Blistering Love"</li>
                <li>"A Like Supreme"</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Maintain good relationship with Rogue</li>
            <li>During "Nocturne Op55N1", choose to ask Rogue for help</li>
            <li>Assault Arasaka Tower with Rogue</li>
            <li>Rogue dies during the assault</li>
            <li>At the finale, choose to enter the Well with Johnny</li>
            <li>Choose to return to V's body (reject becoming a digital construct)</li>
          </ol>

          <p><strong>What Happens:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>V survives and becomes a legend in the Afterlife</li>
            <li>V takes over Rogue's role as the top merc in Night City</li>
            <li>V's apartment becomes a shrine to their legend</li>
            <li>Johnny's engram is removed and destroyed</li>
            <li>V is alone but successful</li>
          </ul>

          <p><strong>Consequences:</strong> V lives but is isolated. They've achieved their dream of being a legend, but they've lost their friends and connections. It's a bittersweet victory.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ending-card">
        <h3>😈 The Devil Ending (Arasaka Path)</h3>
        <div class="ending-info">
          <p><strong>How to Unlock:</strong></p>
          <ol>
            <li>During "Nocturne Op55N1", choose to trust Hanako Arasaka</li>
            <li>Meet Hanako at Embers restaurant</li>
            <li>Hanako betrays you (she works for Arasaka)</li>
            <li>V is captured and taken to Arasaka Tower</li>
            <li>Hanako helps V escape (she has her own agenda)</li>
            <li>Assault Arasaka Tower with Hanako's help</li>
            <li>At the finale, you have two choices:
              <ul>
                <li><strong>Return to V's body:</strong> V survives with 6 months to live</li>
                <li><strong> Become a digital construct:</strong> V's consciousness is uploaded to Mikoshi (secret ending)</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ol>

          <p><strong>What Happens (Return to Body):</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>V survives but has only 6 months to live</li>
            <li>V is completely alone — all friends are gone or dead</li>
            <li>V has no support network and no hope</li>
            <li>Johnny's engram is removed and destroyed</li>
          </ul>

          <p><strong>What Happens (Digital Construct):</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>V's body dies</li>
            <li>V's consciousness exists in Mikoshi (a digital prison)</li>
            <li>V is trapped forever, unable to die but unable to live</li>
            <li>This is the worst ending</li>
          </ul>

          <p><strong>Why It's Bad:</strong> V trusts Arasaka, the company that killed them in the first place. Hanako uses V as a pawn. Even if V survives, they're alone and dying.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ending-card">
        <h3>🌡️ Temperance Ending (Give Body to Johnny)</h3>
        <div class="ending-info">
          <p><strong>How to Unlock:</strong></p>
          <ol>
            <li>Complete any of the above endings</li>
            <li>At the finale, when given the choice, choose to give your body to Johnny</li>
          </ol>

          <p><strong>What Happens:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>V dies</li>
            <li>Johnny Silverhand takes control of V's body</li>
            <li>Johnny leaves Night City (epilogue shows him on a bus)</li>
            <li>Johnny visits V's grave and reflects on his choices</li>
            <li>Johnny smokes a cigarette and walks away</li>
          </ul>

          <p><strong>Consequences:</strong> V is dead, but Johnny gets a second chance at life. It's a selfless act — V sacrifices themselves so Johnny can live. Whether this is a "good" ending depends on your perspective.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ending-card">
        <h3>💀 (Don't Fear) The Reaper (Secret Ending)</h3>
        <div class="ending-info">
          <p><strong>How to Unlock:</strong></p>
          <ol>
            <li>Complete Johnny's side quest "Chippin' In" (during Act 2)</li>
            <li>Make specific dialogue choices during "Chippin' In":
              <ul>
                <li>When Johnny asks "What would you do?", choose: "Nah, man. I don't wanna be a merc."</li>
                <li>When Johnny asks about the oil fields, choose: "Let's do it."</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Increase your relationship with Johnny to at least 70% (shown in the Relationship menu)</li>
            <li>During "Nocturne Op55N1", wait for Johnny to suggest the solo assault option</li>
            <li>If your relationship is high enough, Johnny will suggest storming Arasaka Tower alone</li>
            <li>Choose the "(Don't Fear) The Reaper" option</li>
          </ol>

          <p><strong>What Happens:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li>V assaults Arasaka Tower alone (with Johnny's help)</li>
            <li>This is the hardest combat challenge in the game</li>
            <li>If you succeed, V reaches the top and faces Adam Smasher</li>
            <li>After defeating Smasher, V enters the Well</li>
            <li>At the finale, you can choose any of the other endings (Star, Sun, or Devil)</li>
          </ul>

          <p><strong>Why It's Special:</strong> This ending is only available if you've built a strong relationship with Johnny. It's the most challenging ending and requires completing specific side quests. The combat is brutal but rewarding.</p>

          <div class="tip-box">
            <strong>💡 Combat Tips:</strong>
            <ul>
              <li>Use stealth where possible — you're alone and can't afford to take too much damage</li>
              <li>Bring plenty of health items and cyberware cooldown reductions</li>
              <li>Adam Smasher is the hardest boss in the game. Use hit-and-run tactics and avoid his AoE attacks</li>
              <li>Save before the final assault — you'll want to retry if you die</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="consequences">
      <h2>🔗 Character Fates by Ending</h2>

      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Character</th>
          <th>The Star</th>
          <th>The Sun</th>
          <th>The Devil</th>
          <th>Temperance</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>V</strong></td>
          <td>Leaves with Aldecaldos (6 months to live)</td>
          <td>Becomes Afterlife legend (6 months to live)</td>
          <td>Alone and dying (or digital prison)</td>
          <td>Dead</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Johnny</strong></td>
          <td>Destroyed</td>
          <td>Destroyed</td>
          <td>Destroyed</td>
          <td>Lives in V's body</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Panam</strong></td>
          <td>Survives, becomes V's partner</td>
          <td>Survives, but V leaves her</td>
          <td>Survives, but relationship ends</td>
          <td>Survives, mourns V</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Judy</strong></td>
          <td>Survives, leaves Night City with V</td>
          <td>Survives, but V leaves her</td>
          <td>Survives, but relationship ends</td>
          <td>Survives, mourns V</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>River</strong></td>
          <td>Survives, can romance V</td>
          <td>Survives, but V leaves him</td>
          <td>Survives, but relationship ends</td>
          <td>Survives, mourns V</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Kerry</strong></td>
          <td>Survives, can romance V</td>
          <td>Survives, but V leaves him</td>
          <td>Survives, but relationship ends</td>
          <td>Survives, mourns V</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Rogue</strong></td>
          <td>Survives</td>
          <td>Dies during assault</td>
          <td>Survives</td>
          <td>Survives</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="recommendations">
      <h2>💡 Which Ending Should You Choose?</h2>

      <div class="recommendation">
        <h3>🎯 First Playthrough</h3>
        <p><strong>Choose:</strong> The Star ending</p>
        <p><strong>Why:</strong> It's the most hopeful and complete ending. V survives, has a support network, and leaves with a sense of purpose. It's also the easiest to unlock.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="recommendation">
        <h3>🎯 Completionist Playthrough</h3>
        <p><strong>Choose:</strong> (Don't Fear) The Reaper → The Star</p>
        <p><strong>Why:</strong> You get to experience the secret ending's challenging combat, then still get the best outcome for V.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="recommendation">
        <h3>🎯 Roleplaying as a Mercenary</h3>
        <p><strong>Choose:</strong> The Sun ending</p>
        <p><strong>Why:</strong> If you've been playing V as a ruthless merc trying to become a legend, this ending fits that arc. V achieves their goal but at a cost.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="recommendation">
        <h3>🎯 Roleplaying as Selfless</h3>
        <p><strong>Choose:</strong> Temperance ending</p>
        <p><strong>Why:</strong> If you've built a strong relationship with Johnny and want to give him a second chance, this is the most selfless choice. V sacrifices themselves for Johnny.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tips">
      <h2>💡 Tips for Unlocking All Endings</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Save frequently.</strong> Keep multiple save files so you can reload and choose different endings without replaying the entire game.</li>
        <li><strong>Complete side quests early.</strong> Panam, Rogue, and Johnny's questlines must be completed before the finale. Do them during Act 2.</li>
        <li><strong>Make relationship choices count.</strong> Dialogue choices matter. Be supportive, empathetic, and loyal to build relationships.</li>
        <li><strong>Don't ignore Johnny.</strong> Talk to Johnny frequently and make choices that align with his values to increase your relationship meter.</li>
        <li><strong>Use the point of no return.</strong> The game warns you before the finale. Complete all side quests before crossing this threshold.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <div class="final-note">
      <h2>🎬 Final Thoughts</h2>
      <p>Cyberpunk 2077's endings are bittersweet — there's no "perfect" happy ending. Each ending has its own trade-offs, and the "best" ending depends on your interpretation of V's journey. The Star is the most hopeful, but The Sun fits the mercenary fantasy, and Temperance is the most selfless.</p>
      <p>No matter which ending you choose, you've experienced one of the most ambitious stories in gaming. Good luck, choom.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .guide {
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .intro {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .warning-box {
    background: #fff3cd;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #ffc107;
  }

  .endings-overview table {
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .ending-card {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #fcee09;
  }

  .ending-card h3 {
    color: #fcee09;
    border: none;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .ending-info {
    background: white;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .tip-box {
    background: #d4edda;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #28a745;
  }

  .consequences table {
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .recommendation {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #28a745;
  }

  .final-note {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #16213e 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .final-note h2 {
    color: #fcee09;
    border: none;
  }
</style>
